# Implementation Plan - Align Vehicle Data with AppSheet

[Goal Description]
Update the vehicle (dump truck) data structure and registration forms to match the user's AppSheet source.
Spreadsheet Columns identified: `TruckID`, `車両ナンバー`, `車種`, `積載容量m3`, `会社名`, `ドライバー名`.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> The spreadsheet uses "積載容量m3" (Volume) instead of "積載量(t)" (Weight). I will update the labels to reflect "m3" or generic "Capacity".
> "車種" (Vehicle Type) in the sheet contains values like "10t", "7t", but also "大型ダンプ". I will verify if this maps to the `category` field.

## Proposed Changes

### Logic Layer
#### [MODIFY] [app.js](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/app.js)
- Update [fetchAppSheetMasters](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/app.js#91-113) to map:
    - `TruckID` -> `id` (new field)
    - `車両ナンバー` -> `name`
    - `車種` -> `category`
    - `積載容量m3` -> `capacity` (store as is, e.g., "10")
    - `会社名` -> `company`
    - `ドライバー名` -> `driver`
- Update [sendToAppSheet](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/app.js#114-133) to include these fields when sending data back (if applicable).
- Update [updateFormOptions](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/app.js#292-370) and event listeners to auto-fill these new fields (`m3`, `id`) when a truck is selected.

### UI Layer
#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/index.html)
- Update "Dump Truck Master Registration" modal (`#add-truck-form`):
    - Add input for `TruckID` (optional or auto-gen if manual).
    - Change "Capacity" label to "積載容量 (m3)".
    - Ensure "Vehicle Type" (`category`) allows free text or matches the spreadsheet examples ("10t", "7t", "大型ダンプ").
- Update "New Lot Registration" modal (`#add-lot-form`) for Dump specific fields:
    - Match valid fields (Driver, Capacity m3, etc.).

